</div>
<h2>5. July 7 (Orange): Reinforcement Within Macro Structure</h2>
<p>The July 7 anchor formed within the broader structural environment established by May. Unlike the May distribution, the July dispersion profile is narrower and more reactive. The slope accelerated more quickly, suggesting reinforcement rather than foundational transfer.</p>
<p>Importantly, the July anchor remained nested above May. This nesting dynamic indicates that the July cohort did not replace the macro base; it compounded it. The Orange layer reflects a phase of structural reinforcement and momentum amplification within an intact regime.</p>
<p>Deviation responses within this channel were statistically contained. Lower-band tests were shallow and brief, followed by expansion. This pattern implies responsive buying at controlled stretch rather than structural fragility.</p>
<p>The nesting of July above May establishes a hierarchy: if weakness emerges, migration would be expected toward July before challenging the deeper Green base. The sequential nature of such migration is central to layered regime interpretation.</p>
<hr>
<div class="figure">
  <img data-lightbox src="assets/img/sep23-yellow.png" data-full="assets/img/sep23-yellow.png" data-title="September 23 (Yellow) — Mature Balance Phase" alt="September 23 (Yellow) — Mature Balance Phase">
