</div>
<h2>6. September 23 (Yellow): Equilibrium and Value Rotation</h2>
<p>The September 23 anchor marks a transition from acceleration to equilibrium. Its dispersion envelope is tighter than May and its slope more moderated than July. Price oscillated symmetrically around this mean for extended periods.</p>
<p>This behavior is characteristic of mature balance. The auction spent time establishing value rather than extending trend. Sigma excursions beyond ±2 were limited in duration and typically reverted efficiently toward equilibrium.</p>
<p>The Yellow layer thus functions as an intermediate equilibrium axis. When tactical layers weaken, price often rotates toward this cost basis before testing deeper structural anchors. Such migration is not collapse but redistribution.</p>
<p>The September anchor remains structurally intact as of the documented snapshot. Sustained acceptance below this layer would represent a meaningful escalation in structural pressure. Absent that condition, weakness remains contained within higher-frequency layers.</p>
<hr>
<div class="figure">
