<h2>7. November 28 (Light Blue): Tactical Dominance and Isolated Decay</h2>
<p>The November 28 anchor initially displayed high structural coherence. Dispersion was narrow, mean respect consistent, and rotational behavior orderly. For months, price interacted with this anchored mean as a tactical axis.</p>
<p>Recent developments, however, have altered that profile. Multi-session acceptance below the Light Blue mean represents the first prolonged inability of this cohort to reclaim equilibrium. Unlike earlier probes, the current structure demonstrates sustained trade beneath cost basis.</p>
<p>This shift implies cohort stress. Inventory accumulated since November 28 is increasingly underwater, and rallies toward the mean exhibit supply characteristics rather than responsive demand.</p>
<p>Crucially, this decay remains isolated to the Light Blue layer. The Yellow, Orange, and Green anchors have not experienced comparable acceptance failure. Therefore, while tactical control has weakened, structural regime integrity remains intact.</p>
<hr>
